Brown ground beef in a large skillet. Drain fat. Stir in seasoning mix, tomato paste and water. Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Stir in corn. Preheat oven to 425 degrees F. Place bread shell or pizza crust on baking sheet. Spoon beef mixture over top; sprinkle with cheese. Bake 12-15 minutes or until cheese is melted. Sprinkle with green onions, if desired. Cut into 8 wedges.